RAHEDEEN INVENTORY SAAS - ARCHITECTURE ANALYSIS REPORT
Generated: 2026-03-10

1) PROJECT OVERVIEW

What this project is:
- Multi-tenant SaaS inventory/sales platform.
- Tenant app modules: products, sales, inventory, customers, reports, invoices, alerts, settings.
- Super-admin control plane: tenant metrics, tenant requests, cross-tenant platform monitoring.
- Hybrid backend model:
  - Supabase Auth + Postgres + Edge Functions.
  - Dedicated NestJS API for protected platform endpoints.

Evidence:
- src/App.tsx#L103
- src/views/SuperAdminDashboard.tsx#L121
- apps/api/src/modules/platform-super-admin/platform-super-admin.controller.ts#L8

Tech stack and key dependencies:
- Next.js 15 App Router shell: app/layout.tsx#L26
- Legacy React app mounted via catch-all route: app/[[...slug]]/page.tsx#L5
- React 18 + react-router-dom + @tanstack/react-query: src/App.tsx#L7, src/App.tsx#L40
- Supabase JS client: src/integrations/supabase/client.ts#L2
- NestJS + pg backend: apps/api/package.json#L13
- Supabase Edge Functions (Deno): supabase/functions/*
- CI/CD and process management: .github/workflows/deploy.yml#L95, Ecosystem.config.js#L4

Folder/module structure:
- app/ -> Next shell + middleware + health route
- src/ -> React app domain code (views/hooks/components/utils/libs)
- apps/api/ -> Nest API modules, guards, services, DB infra
- supabase/ -> migrations, edge functions, config
- scripts/ -> local dev orchestration, helpers
- .github/workflows/ -> CI gates, deploy, migration, edge-function deploy

2) CODE FLOW ANALYSIS

Runtime entry points:
1. Web shell:
   - app/layout.tsx#L26
   - app/[[...slug]]/page.tsx#L5
2. React composition root:
   - src/next/LegacyAppClient.tsx#L10
   - src/App.tsx#L187
3. Nest API:
   - apps/api/src/main.ts#L8

Execution path (web):
1. Next catch-all route dynamically imports legacy app client (app/[[...slug]]/page.tsx#L10).
2. LegacyAppClient initializes PWA/theme and mounts App in ErrorBoundary
   (src/next/LegacyAppClient.tsx#L20, src/next/LegacyAppClient.tsx#L25).
3. App wires providers (QueryClient, Theme, Auth, Settings, Router) (src/App.tsx#L188).
4. ProtectedRoute enforces auth/role/tenant/permission checks
   (src/App.tsx#L121, src/components/ProtectedRoute.tsx#L19).
5. /super-admin mounts SuperAdminDashboard (src/App.tsx#L174).
6. Dashboard calls invokeProtectedApi for overview/tenants/detail
   (src/views/SuperAdminDashboard.tsx#L123, src/utils/invokeProtectedApi.ts#L97).

Execution path (API):
1. Nest bootstrap applies CORS + /api global prefix + ValidationPipe
   (apps/api/src/main.ts#L19, apps/api/src/main.ts#L35).
2. AppModule registers guards/controllers/services (apps/api/src/app.module.ts#L17).
3. Super-admin routes pass JwtGuard + RolesGuard
   (apps/api/src/modules/platform-super-admin/platform-super-admin.controller.ts#L9).
4. Controller delegates to service
   (apps/api/src/modules/platform-super-admin/platform-super-admin.controller.ts#L16).
5. Service executes SQL through PlatformDbService
   (apps/api/src/modules/platform-super-admin/platform-super-admin.service.ts#L31,
    apps/api/src/infra/database/platform-db.service.ts#L121).

Major modules:
- AuthProvider: src/hooks/useAuth.tsx#L41
